● Labels and selectors are mechanisms used for identifying and grouping resources, such as pods, services,
  and nodes, based on user-defined key-value pairs
  ○ Labels are key-value paris attached to resources
  ○ Selectors are used to filter and select resources based on their labels
● Annotations are metadata that you can attach to resources such as pods, services, nodes,
  or any other Kubernetes objects
● It is intended for additional data or information that provides context, documentation,
  or other auxiliary details about the resource
● It is typically not used for querying or selecting resources.
